HEADER
    MagicNumber : 0X7777
    ECS_CLIENT_ID : 1 char ...
    Action : 1 char
    Body-length : nb octet
BODY
[

]

OX02 | 1 | INPUT | 8 | [CLEMENT]

ACTIONS COMMUNES (0x01 -> 0x55)
0x01 : NEW CONNECTION
0x02 : DELETE ENTITY

ALL ACTIONS (SERVER TO CLIENT 0x56 -> 0xAA)
0x56 : NEW ENTITY

ALL ACTIONS (CLIENT TO SERVER 0xAA -> 0xFF)
0xAA : INPUT
0xAB : USERNAME


```cpp
struct Header {
    uint16_t MagicNumber;
    uint8_t ECS_CLIENT_ID;
    uint8_t Action;
    uint32_t BodyLength;
};

void *body = malloc(header.BodyLength);
```

For the first connection, the server will send the id of the client on TCP

```cpp
header.MagicNumber = 0x7777;
header.ECS_CLIENT_ID = NEW_ID;
header.Action = 0x01;
header.BodyLength = 0;
body = NULL;
```

And after the client will send the ID of himself on UDP

```cpp
header.MagicNumber = 0x7777;
header.ECS_CLIENT_ID = CLIENT_ID;
header.Action = 0x01;
header.BodyLength = 0;
body = NULL;
```
